        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 21 at 9:47AM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 945 AM EDT, Doppler radar indicated the leading edge of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 10 miles north of
Caseville to Applegate to near Richmond. Movement was east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds near 30 mph and half inch hail in the strongest
storms. Heavy rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs. Minor damage to
outdoor objects is possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Richmond, Bad Axe, Croswell, Lexington, Ubly, Deckerville,
Memphis, Carsonville, Kinde, and Applegate around 950 AM EDT.
Port Austin and Port Sanilac around 955 AM EDT.
Lakeport around 1000 AM EDT.
Forestville and Marysville around 1010 AM EDT.
Port Huron and St. Clair around 1015 AM EDT.
Marine City around 1020 AM EDT.
Harbor Beach and Port Hope around 1025 AM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Goodland Township,
Huron City, White Rock, Rapson, Grindstone City, Ray Center, Amador,
Ellington, Juhl, and Silverwood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
